comments.body:
Thanks @jhoneill ! Love the solution. And I agree with @dwtaber to have it as built-in function.

@daxian-dbw Do you mean this option in windows update settings?
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10512841/170432408-e5b02230-9c21-40d9-88bb-3099022f0cd8.png)

@doctordns  Not sure what the best way is but if you've seen this https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell-RFC/pull/324/files 
Jason is trying to get an "install current PowerShell" included with **Windows PowerShell 5** to get round the "Windows life > .net life" issue which prevents PowerShell 7 going in the box with windows and sends people round the houses to get it. 

That proposal is trying to avoid scope creep but the same command should be runnable in any version of PowerShell and get the latest.
